snippet.textDisplay: I've been making fancy/mad cakes for my friends and family for over 30. What I discovered in all that time is that cake mix is the best way to get a consistent cake over many layers. If you need a lot of layers in a uniform size and density, it's the easiest to use mixes, if you don't have access to a professional bakery kitchen. You can add your own twist to them, but I've also discovered that no-one notices. Not a single person. XD
snippet.textOriginal: I've been making fancy/mad cakes for my friends and family for over 30. What I discovered in all that time is that cake mix is the best way to get a consistent cake over many layers. If you need a lot of layers in a uniform size and density, it's the easiest to use mixes, if you don't have access to a professional bakery kitchen.
